{
  "stem": "8252.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They didn't take anybody to any camps or anything like that, but it was a day work, a full day and a hard work and, you know, with a German guard.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were not used to it yet, at that point.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So but I, I decided to brave it, and I took my passport and my mother's passport.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, by the way, when Ribbentrop and Molotov signed the non-aggression pact, my, my family here in the States rushed and got a visa for my mother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They couldn't get a visa for me, but they got a visa for my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was supposed to go to America on the 3rd of September, but the boat that was supposed to take her didn't come in.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was with me in Lodz with the visa to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she had the visa and her passport I had no visa.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I braved this thing and went well and I got my extension of my Polish foreign passport, going to abroad, a special passport.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I also got a visa through Germany, which I didn't know I needed at all.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So then I was told that to get out of there, I needed a visa of-- I had the passage through Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I needed a visa to any country to get out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I started thinking where I can go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A lot of my friends were going east, away from the Germans and trying to penetrate into Russia-- into Soviet Union at that time.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
